hurch. Part 5 concludes with the start of the reign of Emperor Theodosius and the edict conctos populos.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Ancient (to 1453).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aAnhomöer. 4aArianismus. 4aKonzile. 4aNeunizänismus. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh  aArianismus.  aSynoden.  aTrinitätslehre.1 aBrennecke, Hanns Christof, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeil, Uta.1 aMüller, Christian.1 aStockhausen, Annette, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311059228340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311059856840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110598568423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110598568.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020